Windows OS-Level Pause Menu - Complete Implementation Plan (Tauri + Rust)
Project Overview
Technology Stack: Tauri + Rust + TypeScript + React

Platform: Windows (V1), macOS (V2), iOS/Android (V3)

Architecture: Desktop app (Tauri) + Backend API + Payment processing

---

Phase 1: Project Setup & Foundation
1.1 Development Environment Setup
Prerequisites Installation:

[ ] Rust toolchain (rustup) - https://rustup.rs/
[ ] Visual C++ Build Tools - Already installed ✅
[ ] Git - https://git-scm.com/download/win
[ ] Node.js 18+ LTS - https://nodejs.org/
[ ] Cursor IDE with extensions:
[ ] rust-analyzer extension
[ ] Tauri extension
[ ] CodeLLDB extension (debugging)
Verify Installation:

rustc --version
cargo --version
node --version
npm --version
git --version
1.2 Tauri Project Initialization
Create Project:

npm create tauri-app@latest pause-menu
Project Configuration:

[ ] Project name: pause-menu
[ ] UI framework: React (with TypeScript)
[ ] Package manager: npm
[ ] Tauri version: Latest stable
Project Structure:

pause-menu/
├── src/                          # Frontend (React + TypeScript)
│   ├── components/              # React components
