Phase 2: Core OS Integration (Rust Backend)
2.1 Global Keyboard Shortcut (Win + Space)
Implementation: src-tauri/src/services/shortcut_manager.rs

Features:

[ ] Register Win+Space global shortcut
[ ] Works from any application
[ ] Works in fullscreen mode
[ ] Works across multiple monitors
[ ] Emit event to frontend when triggered
Tauri Plugin:

[ ] Install @tauri-apps/plugin-global-shortcut
[ ] Configure in tauri.conf.json
[ ] Register shortcut in Rust backend
[ ] Handle shortcut press event
[ ] Send event to frontend via Tauri IPC
Code Structure:

// Register shortcut
let shortcut = GlobalShortcut::new("Super+Space")?;
app.handle().global_shortcut().register(shortcut, |app| {
    // Emit event to frontend
    app.emit("shortcut-triggered", ()).unwrap();
})?;
2.2 System Overlay (Above All Windows)
Implementation: src-tauri/src/services/overlay_manager.rs

Features:

[ ] Create fullscreen overlay window
[ ] Set WS_EX_TOPMOST flag (always on top)
[ ] Set WS_EX_TRANSPARENT flag (click-through when needed)
[ ] Works over fullscreen applications
[ ] Multi-monitor support
[ ] Screen dimming effect
[ ] Smooth fade-in/fade-out animations
Window Configuration:

[ ] Frameless window
[ ] Transparent background
[ ] Fullscreen mode
[ ] Skip taskbar
[ ] No focus (doesn't steal focus)
[ ] High z-order (above all windows)
Tauri Configuration:

{
  "windows": [{
    "fullscreen": true,
    "transparent": true,
    "decorations": false,
    "alwaysOnTop": true,
    "skipTaskbar": true,
    "focusable": false
  }]
}
Windows API Calls:

[ ] Use SetWindowPos with HWND_TOPMOST
[ ] Use SetWindowLongPtr for extended window styles
[ ] Handle multi-monitor scenarios
[ ] Position overlay on all monitors

2.3 Window Tracking & Enumeration
Implementation: src-tauri/src/services/window_tracker.rs

Features:

[ ] Enumerate all open windows
[ ] Get window titles
[ ] Get process names
[ ] Get window handles
[ ] Track window focus changes
[ ] Track window open/close events
[ ] Get window last active time
[ ] Filter visible windows only
Windows API Usage:

[ ] EnumWindows - Enumerate all windows
[ ] GetWindowText - Get window title
[ ] GetWindowThreadProcessId - Get process info
[ ] IsWindowVisible - Filter visible windows
[ ] GetForegroundWindow - Get active window
Data Model:

pub struct WindowInfo {
    pub handle: isize,
    pub title: String,
    pub process_name: String,
    pub executable_path: String,
    pub last_active: DateTime<Utc>,
    pub is_visible: bool,
}
Polling Strategy:

[ ] Poll every 2 seconds for window changes
[ ] Cache window list
[ ] Only send updates when changes detected
[ ] Optimize for performance


2.4 Recent Files Tracking
Implementation: src-tauri/src/services/file_tracker.rs

Features:

[ ] Monitor Windows Recent folder
[ ] Track recently opened files
[ ] Get file metadata (name, path, last accessed)
[ ] Filter by file type
[ ] Lightweight, non-invasive tracking
Tracking Methods:

[ ] Watch %APPDATA%\Microsoft\Windows\Recent folder
[ ] Use notify crate for file system events
[ ] Parse .lnk files (Windows shortcuts)
[ ] Extract target file paths
[ ] Store in memory cache
Data Model:

pub struct RecentFile {
    pub name: String,
    pub path: String,
    pub last_accessed: DateTime<Utc>,
    pub file_type: String,
}
Privacy:

[ ] No file content reading
[ ] Only metadata tracking
[ ] User can disable if needed



