Phase 4: Backend API & Services
4.1 Backend API Setup
Technology: Node.js + Express (or FastAPI)

API Endpoints:

[ ] POST /api/auth/login - Magic link login
[ ] POST /api/auth/verify - Verify magic link
[ ] GET /api/subscription/status - Get subscription status
[ ] POST /api/subscription/webhook - Stripe webhook
[ ] GET /api/user/profile - Get user profile
[ ] POST /api/analytics/event - Track events (optional)
Project Structure:

backend/
├── src/
│   ├── routes/
│   │   ├── auth.ts
│   │   ├── subscription.ts
│   │   └── user.ts
│   ├── services/
│   │   ├── auth.ts
│   │   ├── stripe.ts
│   │   └── email.ts
│   ├── models/
│   │   ├── user.ts
│   │   └── subscription.ts
│   └── server.ts
├── package.json
└── .env
4.2 Authentication (Magic Link)
Implementation: backend/src/services/auth.ts

Features:

[ ] Generate magic link token
[ ] Send email with magic link
[ ] Verify token
[ ] Create user session
[ ] JWT token generation
Flow:

User enters email in desktop app
Backend generates token
Email sent with magic link
User clicks link (opens in browser)
Browser verifies token
Backend creates session
Desktop app receives auth token
Email Service:

[ ] Use SendGrid or similar
[ ] Email template
[ ] Magic link URL
[ ] Expiration (15 minutes)
4.3 Stripe Integration
Implementation: backend/src/services/stripe.ts

Features:

[ ] Create Stripe Checkout session
[ ] Handle webhook events
[ ] Subscription status management
[ ] Pro features unlock
Webhook Events:

[ ] checkout.session.completed - User subscribed
[ ] customer.subscription.updated - Subscription updated
[ ] customer.subscription.deleted - Subscription cancelled
Subscription Tiers:

[ ] Free tier (limited features)
[ ] Pro tier (all features)
[ ] Check subscription on app startup
[ ] Lock/unlock features based on status
4.4 n8n Workflow Automation
n8n Workflows:

1. User Onboarding:

[ ] Trigger: User signs up
[ ] Actions:
Send welcome email
Create user record
Initialize free tier
2. Subscription Lifecycle:

[ ] Trigger: Stripe webhook
[ ] Actions:
Update user subscription status
Send confirmation email
Unlock Pro features
3. App Installed:

[ ] Trigger: App first launch
[ ] Actions:
Send setup guide email
Track installation
Future Workflows:

[ ] Upload notes → LetMeSell pipeline
